.TH BINR 1 "December 2025" "0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
binr \- build rules via stochastic incremental XAI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./binr.py
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIACTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B binr
is a Python script designed for stochastic incremental Explainable AI (XAI). It processes datasets (typically CSV) to build rules, calculate distances, and perform hill-climbing optimization to find best scoring rows.
.PP
The script utilizes a custom object dictionary structure and supports various statistical distributions (Normal, Triangular, Symbolic) for data summarization and sampling.
.SH OPTIONS
The following configuration options modify the global settings (the \fIthe\fR object).
.TP
.B \-h
Show the help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-b \fIbins\fR
Set number of bins for discretization (default: 4).
.TP
.B \-B \fIBudget\fR
Set max rows to evaluate (default: 30).
.TP
.B \-C \fICF\fR
Set crossover rate (default: 0.8).
.TP
.B \-F \fIF\fR
Set scale factor between two numbers (default: 0.3).
.TP
.B \-e \fIera\fR
Set number of rows in an era (default: 10).
.TP
.B \-p \fIp\fR
Set distance coefficient (default: 2).
.TP
.B \-r \fIrepeats\fR
Set number of experimental repeats (default: 20).
.TP
.B \-s \fIseed\fR
Set random number seed (default: 42).
.TP
.B \-f \fIfile\fR
Set file path to load data from (default: ../data/auto93.csv).
.SH ACTIONS
The script uses a dynamic dispatcher to run functions based on command line arguments. Double-dash arguments typically correspond to test functions or specific demos.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Run all available test functions.
.TP
.B \-\-the
Print the current global configuration settings.
.TP
.B \-\-sym
Demonstrate the Symbolic (Sym) distribution summary.
.TP
.B \-\-num
Demonstrate the Numeric (Num) distribution summary using Irwin-Hall sampling.
.TP
.B \-\-data
Load the dataset and print summary statistics for the last X column.
.TP
.B \-\-disty
Calculate and print distances of rows to the "best" values in goal columns (Y-distance).
.TP
.B \-\-distx
Calculate and print distances between X attributes of rows.
.TP
.B \-\-inc
Demonstrate incremental updates (adding/subtracting rows) to the Data structure.
.TP
.B \-\-random
Perform random sampling on a defined model and select the best result.
.TP
.B \-\-hclimb
Perform a stochastic hill-climbing algorithm to optimize row selection.
.TP
.B \-\-score
Calculate scores for data rows and attempt to predict next best scores.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B View help:
.RS
\&./binr.py -h
.RE
.PP
.B Run all tests:
.RS
\&./binr.py --all
.RE
.PP
.B Run the hill climber with a specific seed:
.RS
\&./binr.py -s 12345 --hclimb
.RE
